01:13:27.385 --> 01:13:31.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
the graduates of the 156th class of Gilead.

01:13:53.328 --> 01:13:56.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, the class has written a letter
that they would like to read.

01:13:56.456 --> 01:13:59.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so Brother Louis Walker from
the United States will read that for us now.

01:14:10.345 --> 01:14:13.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
“To the Governing Body and Bethel family:

01:14:15.267 --> 01:14:18.812 line:90% position:50% align:center
“After five months of intense Bible study,

01:14:18.812 --> 01:14:21.940 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we are filled with so many emotions

01:14:21.940 --> 01:14:24.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that it is hard to find words to express

01:14:24.067 --> 01:14:27.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
“our appreciation and gratitude.

01:14:27.571 --> 01:14:29.948 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We feel like Isaiah

01:14:29.948 --> 01:14:34.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
“when he saw a vision of Jehovah
as described in Isaiah chapter 6.

01:14:35.078 --> 01:14:39.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He saw Jehovah in a way he never had before,

01:14:39.082 --> 01:14:42.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and the same is true of us.

01:14:42.002 --> 01:14:45.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Gilead has helped us
to more deeply appreciate

01:14:45.756 --> 01:14:48.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jehovah’s beautiful personality,

01:14:48.967 --> 01:14:51.428 line:90% position:50% align:center
“his matchless wisdom,

01:14:51.428 --> 01:14:54.139 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and his unfailing love.

01:14:54.139 --> 01:14:56.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Like Isaiah, at times

01:14:56.475 --> 01:15:00.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we felt overwhelmed
with our imperfections and limitations.

01:15:00.854 --> 01:15:05.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
“However, just as Jehovah
reassured Isaiah through a seraph,

01:15:06.860 --> 01:15:09.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jehovah lovingly encouraged us.

01:15:10.239 --> 01:15:14.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
“During the past 20 weeks, we were cared for

01:15:14.952 --> 01:15:17.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
“as ‘a nursing mother tenderly cares

01:15:17.955 --> 01:15:19.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for her own children.’

01:15:19.999 --> 01:15:24.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Our instructors became ‘beloved to us’

01:15:24.461 --> 01:15:28.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
“as they shared not only their knowledge
and understanding of God’s Word

01:15:28.757 --> 01:15:31.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but their ‘very selves.’

01:15:31.135 --> 01:15:35.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We were encouraged 
to always give Jehovah our best,

01:15:35.181 --> 01:15:39.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to lower ourselves, and to lift others up.

01:15:40.436 --> 01:15:44.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We learned the value 
of not taking ourselves too seriously

01:15:44.190 --> 01:15:47.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and to cherish our journey with Jehovah.

01:15:49.111 --> 01:15:53.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We also deeply appreciate
our dear Governing Body.

01:15:54.784 --> 01:15:58.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Despite your very busy schedules,

01:15:58.162 --> 01:16:00.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
“you made time for us.

01:16:00.957 --> 01:16:04.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Your heartfelt lectures motivated us

01:16:04.001 --> 01:16:06.337 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to be courageous

01:16:06.337 --> 01:16:09.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and to not fear the challenges we will face.

01:16:10.425 --> 01:16:14.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We will never forget
your example of kindness,

01:16:14.095 --> 01:16:16.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
“humility, and love.

01:16:18.057 --> 01:16:20.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
“In ‘imitating your faith,’

01:16:20.685 --> 01:16:24.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we are determined to remain loyal

01:16:24.022 --> 01:16:27.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and submissive
to Jehovah and his organization

01:16:27.483 --> 01:16:29.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
“as we go out to our assignments.

01:16:31.237 --> 01:16:35.825 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Finally, our education
went beyond the Gilead classroom.

01:16:36.826 --> 01:16:39.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We saw hospitality defined

01:16:39.662 --> 01:16:43.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
“by you dear brothers and sisters
of the United States Bethel family.

01:16:44.918 --> 01:16:49.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Your kindness and generosity
were outstanding!

01:16:50.131 --> 01:16:52.509 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We were simply basking in your love.

01:16:53.885 --> 01:16:58.056 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And although we did not have enough time
to get to know each one of you,

01:16:58.056 --> 01:17:00.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
“it was enough time to fall in love with you.

01:17:02.769 --> 01:17:07.607 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We will never be able
to thank our heavenly Father enough

01:17:07.607 --> 01:17:10.610 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for this unique experience!

01:17:10.610 --> 01:17:14.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We now echo the words of Isaiah,
who declared

01:17:14.447 --> 01:17:18.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
“even before receiving details
of his new assignment:

01:17:22.831 --> 01:17:24.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Here I am!
Send me!

01:17:24.833 --> 01:17:26.752 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Send me!’

01:17:26.752 --> 01:17:29.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
“As we depart for our respective assignments,

01:17:29.921 --> 01:17:34.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we are confident,
thanks to this beautiful training,

01:17:34.718 --> 01:17:39.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that Jehovah ‘will make us firm
and he will make us strong.’

01:17:40.641 --> 01:17:43.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
“With hearts full of gratitude and love,

01:17:43.769 --> 01:17:47.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
your brothers, the 156th class of Gilead.”

01:18:23.100 --> 01:18:25.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we thank you for those sentiments.

01:18:25.227 --> 01:18:27.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
It truly does reflect the appreciation

01:18:27.688 --> 01:18:32.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
and spirituality of the entire class,
so we appreciate that very much.

01:18:32.401 --> 01:18:34.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what a pleasure to be with you today!

01:18:35.237 --> 01:18:37.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, in our opening comments,
we talked a bit

01:18:37.740 --> 01:18:42.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
about the privilege of being ones
whom Jehovah would use.

01:18:42.078 --> 01:18:45.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
And remember, we reviewed examples
from Luke chapters 1 and 2

01:18:45.539 --> 01:18:48.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
of humble, obedient ones
whom Jehovah appreciated,

01:18:48.751 --> 01:18:53.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
like Mary, the humble shepherds,
Simeon, and Anna.

01:18:53.589 --> 01:18:57.343 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the encouragement
was to imitate those fine examples,

01:18:57.343 --> 01:19:01.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
and be the kind of people
whom Jehovah is pleased to use

01:19:01.597 --> 01:19:05.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
by cultivating what matters most to Jehovah,

01:19:05.726 --> 01:19:08.813 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is,
spiritual qualities that he holds dear

01:19:08.813 --> 01:19:11.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that makes us useful to him.

01:19:13.276 --> 01:19:16.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the fact is, you are ones

01:19:16.529 --> 01:19:18.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
whom Jehovah is pleased to use.

01:19:19.615 --> 01:19:21.743 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, all of Jehovah’s people

01:19:21.743 --> 01:19:25.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
—all in the listening audience,
all of Jehovah’s people the world over—

01:19:25.204 --> 01:19:29.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah is pleased to use
because he has drawn each one.

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:29.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that, don’t we?

01:19:29.876 --> 01:19:32.503 line:90% position:50% align:center
John 6:44 tells us
(what does the verse say?):

01:19:32.503 --> 01:19:35.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
“No man can come to me unless the Father,
who sent me,

01:19:35.256 --> 01:19:38.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
draws him,
and I will resurrect him on the last day.”

01:19:38.426 --> 01:19:41.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Jehovah has drawn each one of us

01:19:41.846 --> 01:19:45.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
because he saw something
in our hearts of value.

01:19:45.850 --> 01:19:48.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
He saw a humility and honesty

01:19:48.561 --> 01:19:53.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
and a desire to learn the truth
and to serve the true and living God.

01:19:53.775 --> 01:19:56.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so we have the privilege, then,

01:19:56.403 --> 01:20:00.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
of being a part of Jehovah’s name people.

01:20:00.365 --> 01:20:03.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
As individuals,
we have the privilege of having a place

01:20:03.201 --> 01:20:05.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
in his great spiritual temple arrangement.

01:20:05.829 --> 01:20:09.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
We are all on Jehovah’s team,

01:20:09.249 --> 01:20:12.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the privilege that every one of us has,
of course,

01:20:12.127 --> 01:20:14.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
is to bear his name
in the Kingdom preaching work.

01:20:16.882 --> 01:20:19.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
But at times,
Jehovah also gives us other work to do

01:20:19.801 --> 01:20:23.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
in other assignments that are
related to the Kingdom preaching work.

01:20:23.180 --> 01:20:25.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
And for you, dear friends, that included

01:20:25.474 --> 01:20:28.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
providing to you this training in Gilead.

01:20:29.644 --> 01:20:32.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
And while this Gilead training
doesn’t place you above your brothers

01:20:32.147 --> 01:20:34.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
—and you certainly do not feel that way—

01:20:34.441 --> 01:20:37.736 line:90% position:50% align:center
it does indicate Jehovah’s approval of you

01:20:37.736 --> 01:20:41.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the fact that he saw something good
in your hearts

01:20:41.198 --> 01:20:44.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he could then continue to mold and train

01:20:44.368 --> 01:20:46.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that he could use you to further help

01:20:46.495 --> 01:20:49.206 line:90% position:50% align:center
and strengthen his people.

01:20:49.206 --> 01:20:52.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
And quite likely it’s some of the same things
that he saw in Mary

01:20:52.668 --> 01:20:56.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the shepherds and Simeon and Anna:

01:20:56.088 --> 01:20:59.007 line:90% position:50% align:center
humility, deep spirituality, obedience,

01:20:59.007 --> 01:21:02.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
loyalty, appreciation for spiritual things,

01:21:02.094 --> 01:21:06.515 line:90% position:50% align:center
and constancy in your theocratic routine.

01:21:06.515 --> 01:21:09.810 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be assured that Jehovah loves you

01:21:09.810 --> 01:21:14.023 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that he approves of you
for these valuable qualities

01:21:14.023 --> 01:21:16.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
that really make you useful to him.

01:21:18.110 --> 01:21:20.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so our concluding encouragement is

01:21:20.863 --> 01:21:23.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
to keep being the kind of people

01:21:23.157 --> 01:21:25.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
whom Jehovah can use.

01:21:25.784 --> 01:21:28.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
Really,
that’s at the heart of the encouragement

01:21:28.204 --> 01:21:31.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Philippians 3:16: “At any rate,
to the extent we have made progress,

01:21:31.957 --> 01:21:35.586 line:90% position:50% align:center
let us go on walking orderly
in this same [routine].”

01:21:36.670 --> 01:21:39.381 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we think back
to our examples from Luke chapters 1 and 2.

01:21:39.381 --> 01:21:41.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we don’t hear again
about Simeon and Anna,

01:21:41.842 --> 01:21:45.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
although we are sure that they remained
faithful for the rest of their lives.

01:21:45.930 --> 01:21:48.224 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we do follow Mary

01:21:48.224 --> 01:21:51.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
as she continued in her service to Jehovah

01:21:51.060 --> 01:21:53.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the years went by as she raised Jesus

01:21:53.187 --> 01:21:58.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
and her other children along with Joseph
to love and serve Jehovah.

01:21:58.568 --> 01:22:01.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
We watched as Mary appreciatively

01:22:01.487 --> 01:22:04.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘preserved these things in her heart’

01:22:04.198 --> 01:22:07.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah was doing
in connection with her son

01:22:07.702 --> 01:22:10.163 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his Son, of course, Jehovah’s.

01:22:10.163 --> 01:22:14.041 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we also follow Mary as she

01:22:14.041 --> 01:22:17.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
possibly dealt with the death of her husband
at some point along the way 

01:22:17.670 --> 01:22:20.798 line:90% position:50% align:center
and as she dealt
with the initial lack of faith

01:22:20.798 --> 01:22:24.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
of her other children in Jesus’ Messiahship

01:22:24.052 --> 01:22:27.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then finally as she watched her son die

01:22:27.263 --> 01:22:31.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a most shameful and painful way
on that torture stake,

01:22:31.184 --> 01:22:33.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
when Simeon’s words came true

01:22:33.770 --> 01:22:36.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
that ‘a long sword would be run through her.’

01:22:37.607 --> 01:22:40.652 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s confidence in Mary was well-placed.

01:22:40.652 --> 01:22:45.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
She continued to be the kind of person
whom he could use.

01:22:45.240 --> 01:22:47.742 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so follow her good example

01:22:47.742 --> 01:22:50.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
by being one whom Jehovah
can continue to use

01:22:50.412 --> 01:22:53.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
and by focusing
on what matters most to Jehovah.

01:22:53.456 --> 01:22:55.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep cultivating the qualities

01:22:55.792 --> 01:22:58.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
that will endear you to Jehovah.

01:22:58.545 --> 01:23:01.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then whatever work needs to be done,

01:23:01.923 --> 01:23:04.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
whatever assignment needs to be filled,

01:23:04.259 --> 01:23:07.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
whatever encouragement needs to be given,

01:23:07.178 --> 01:23:09.681 line:90% position:50% align:center
well, then, you will be spiritually qualified

01:23:09.681 --> 01:23:14.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you will be ready to be used by Jehovah
if that is his desire.

01:23:14.477 --> 01:23:18.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, continue to be one whom Jehovah
would use in his service,

01:23:18.565 --> 01:23:20.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then you will always have his favor

01:23:20.692 --> 01:23:23.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you will have joy and contentment
in whatever

01:23:23.987 --> 01:23:26.364 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has in mind for you to do.

01:23:27.032 --> 01:23:30.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
We hope you enjoyed
this portion of the graduation.

01:23:31.661 --> 01:23:34.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be on the lookout for the rest of the program

01:23:34.623 --> 01:23:38.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
as it’s released on jw.org during this month.

01:23:39.962 --> 01:23:42.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
To conclude, our postcard

01:23:42.464 --> 01:23:45.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
takes us to the southern tip of Africa.

01:23:45.759 --> 01:23:49.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
Welcome to Eswatini.

01:23:49.137 --> 01:23:51.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
This tiny landlocked country,

01:23:51.431 --> 01:23:54.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
once known as Swaziland,

01:23:54.059 --> 01:23:57.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
sits between Mozambique and South Africa.

01:23:59.606 --> 01:24:01.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can find magnificent wildlife

01:24:01.483 --> 01:24:04.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Hlane National Park

01:24:04.111 --> 01:24:07.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
or stand in amazement

01:24:07.781 --> 01:24:12.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
beside Sibebe Rock,
one of the world’s largest granite domes.

01:24:13.537 --> 01:24:18.292 line:90% position:50% align:center
Tradition has an important place
in Eswatini culture.

01:24:18.917 --> 01:24:22.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
How men or women tie lihiya fabric

01:24:22.296 --> 01:24:24.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
over their shoulders

01:24:24.215 --> 01:24:26.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
communicates whether they are
married or single.

01:24:28.260 --> 01:24:30.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
The country also has kept 

01:24:30.596 --> 01:24:34.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
the tradition of an absolute monarchy.

01:24:34.683 --> 01:24:39.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
King Sobhuza II reigned for 82 years

01:24:39.522 --> 01:24:42.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
until his death in 1982

01:24:42.691 --> 01:24:46.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
and had quite the rapport
with Jehovah’s Witnesses.

01:24:47.154 --> 01:24:49.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1933,

01:24:49.365 --> 01:24:53.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
the king was delighted
with the message carried by pioneers

01:24:53.869 --> 01:24:57.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
and called his personal bodyguard
of 100 warriors

01:24:57.790 --> 01:24:59.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
to listen as well.

01:25:00.668 --> 01:25:02.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
On another occasion,

01:25:02.670 --> 01:25:06.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
he offered to buy
the loudspeaker and the records

01:25:06.507 --> 01:25:09.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
our brothers were using.

01:25:09.135 --> 01:25:11.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
They humbly explained,

01:25:11.804 --> 01:25:15.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It all belongs to another King.”

01:25:15.683 --> 01:25:18.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sobhuza wanted to know who this was.

01:25:19.937 --> 01:25:22.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He is Jesus Christ.”

01:25:22.899 --> 01:25:27.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sobhuza replied: “Oh, he’s a great King.

01:25:27.820 --> 01:25:31.324 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t want to take anything
that belongs to him.”

01:25:32.909 --> 01:25:35.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our brothers continue loyally announcing

01:25:35.828 --> 01:25:37.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
God’s Kingdom.

01:25:37.413 --> 01:25:40.250 line:90% position:50% align:center
Currently, there are

01:25:40.250 --> 01:25:43.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
over 3,000 publishers
conducting

01:25:43.378 --> 01:25:45.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
over 4,000 Bible studies.

01:25:45.839 --> 01:25:48.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
The country also hosts

01:25:48.049 --> 01:25:52.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
refugees from Burundi, Rwanda, Uganda,

01:25:52.262 --> 01:25:54.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
and various other countries.

01:25:55.515 --> 01:25:57.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
And publishers go to the camp

01:25:57.434 --> 01:26:02.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
to preach, extending a warm welcome
and a message of hope.

01:26:03.106 --> 01:26:07.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can feel the love our brothers
in the Nkoyoyo Congregation

01:26:07.694 --> 01:26:11.364 line:90% position:50% align:center
have for neighbor and each other.

01:26:11.364 --> 01:26:15.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
They wish to send that love to you,

01:26:15.202 --> 01:26:17.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
the worldwide brotherhood.

01:26:17.496 --> 01:26:21.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:26:21.708 --> 01:26:24.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting!

